                                Press Release
       _______________________________________________________________

     The Hon. Frederick J. Scullin, Jr., Chief Judge, U.S. District
     Court, N.D.N.Y., is pleased to announce that on Thursday, January
     24, 2002, at an informal ceremony at the James T. Foley Courthouse
     in Albany N.Y., the Hon. Larry Alan Kudrle was sworn in as a
     part-time United States Magistrate Judge for the Northern District
     of New York. Judge Kudrle, a resident of Plattsburgh, N.Y. will
     assume his duties immediately.

     Judge Kudrle is a graduate of Mankato State College, the University
     of Arizona, Texas A&M University and the University of Arizona Law
     School. From July of 1974 to June of 1994, he served in the United
     States Air Force wherein he retired with the rank of Lieutenant
     Colonel. Since his retirement from the Air Force in 1994, he has
     worked at the law firm of Lewis, Rogers, Kudrle and Meconi P.C.
     located in Plattsburgh, N.Y. Mr. Kudrle is married to Suzanne Kudrle
     and has four children.

     A formal investiture will be held later this spring in Plattsburgh.

